ul.li: cpu_state positioned at top of stack, grows into stack
EFLAGS.IF=1 to enable interrupts on first run
State READY before adding to run queue

div.p: proc->pid = next_pid++ proc->state = READY proc->parent_pid = current->pid strncpy(proc->name, name, 31)

0x00102000 kernel_stack_top ESP0 for TSS
4KB Stack grows down
0x00101000 stack_frame frame_alloc()

state->eip = (uint32_t)entry_point state->cs = 0x08 // Kernel CS state->eflags = 0x202 // IF=1 state->esp = proc->kernel_stack_top state->ss = 0x10 // Kernel DS state->ds = es = fs = gs = 0x10 proc->kernel_stack = state;
Return PCB Pointer c return proc; // Ready to schedule!
